The paper deals with the P vs. NP problem and lower bound problems in complexity theory, which are central topics in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves algebraic geometry and representation theory, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The use of obstructions and orbit closures suggests a connection to logic and set theory (cs.LO), and the mention of the Borel-Weil theorem suggests a connection to group theory (cs.GT).
